Testing was performed with the as-prepared electrocatalysts loaded on the gas diffusion layer of the air electrode of an in-house-made ZAB at room temperature. The catalyst ink was prepared as described above and drop-cast onto carbon paper at a mass loading of 1 mg cm−2. The air cathode was coated with a 1:1 (w/w) mixture of 20 wt % Pt/C and 5 wt % Ru/C at the same total catalyst loading. Zn foil was used as the metal anode, and a solution containing 6 M KOH (Guaranteed Reagent, Junsei Co., Ltd.) and 0.2 M zinc acetate (Sigma-Aldrich Co., Ltd.) was used as the electrolyte. Polarization curves were constructed by performing LSV measurements at a sweep rate of 10 mV s−1 using an electrochemical workstation (Biologic, VSP, France). Specific capacity and energy density were calculated as [47] 4Energydensity(mWcm-2)=IVΔt/ωZn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
